335
00:18:19,811 --> 00:18:21,562
其实也没什么关系 不是吗?
It doesn't really matter, does it?

336
00:18:21,596 --> 00:18:24,364
反正她们很快就会死掉
Because they're gonna die soon anyway.

337
00:18:24,399 --> 00:18:27,568
一般都是这个时候 对吧 乔安娜?
It always happens around this time. Right, Joanna?

338
00:18:31,399 --> 00:18:34,625
滴答 滴答
Ticktock. Ticktock.

339
00:18:34,659 --> 00:18:37,544
- 滴答 - 够了
- Ticktock. - That's enough.

340
00:18:37,579 --> 00:18:39,246
我刺激到某人了吗?
Did I strike a nerve?

341
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:43,611
解开束缚
Liber a vinculis.

342
00:18:50,091 --> 00:18:53,005
我感觉很糟糕 我怎么了?  
I feel worse. Wha's wrong with me?  

343
00:18:53,006 --> 00:18:55,295
把这个茶喝了 会管用的
Drink this tea. It'll help.

344
00:18:55,773 --> 00:18:58,453
我的胳膊没有知觉了  
I can't feel my arms. 

345
00:18:58,454 --> 00:19:00,017
嗯 让我帮你吧
Oh, well, let me help.

346
00:19:04,189 --> 00:19:06,788
达什今天给我送花了  
Dash sent me flowers today. 

347
00:19:06,789 --> 00:19:08,442
太好了 亲爱的
Oh, that's wonderful, dear.

348
00:19:08,476 --> 00:19:12,112
- 那他一定是原谅你了 - 他是我的真爱
- That must mean he forgives you. - He's my soul mate.

349
00:19:12,463 --> 00:19:16,483
他当然是 再喝点
Of course he is. Have some more.

350
00:19:18,953 --> 00:19:21,590
我感觉好困
I just feel so sleepy.

351
00:19:22,207 --> 00:19:24,174
我要躺一会
I'm gonna lay down.

352
00:19:24,714 --> 00:19:28,183
很好 你睡吧
Oh, that's good. You sleep.

353
00:19:50,896 --> 00:19:54,812
酒精稀释...
Vinum attenuat...

354
00:19:55,404 --> 00:19:57,772
...调剂
...Eam.

355
00:20:00,023 --> 00:20:01,991
嗨
Hey.

356
00:20:02,413 --> 00:20:04,832
我很快就走 我保证
I'm leaving soon. I promise.

357
00:20:04,866 --> 00:20:08,151
只是... 这比我旅馆的房间好多了
It's just... it's so much nicer here than my hotel room.

358
00:20:08,152 --> 00:20:11,664
慢慢来 我又发现一本书可能会有用
Take your time. I found one more that might be useful.

359
00:20:11,689 --> 00:20:13,004
太好了
Great.

360
00:20:15,830 --> 00:20:17,544
我没告诉你我的论文
I did not tell you about my dissertation,

361
00:20:17,562 --> 00:20:20,046
你也没告诉我你是一个出版作家
but you didn't tell me you're a published author.

362
00:20:20,064 --> 00:20:22,399
想不到真有图书馆会收藏这本书
I can't believe there's a library that actually stocks this.

363
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:24,370
它不怎么畅销
It wasn't exactly a bestseller.

364
00:20:24,371 --> 00:20:27,387
是啊 我们有呢 而且我希望你能帮我签名
Well, we have it, and I would like for you to sign it for me.

365
00:20:28,503 --> 00:20:31,249
图书馆不是有规定不能在书上写字吗?
Isn't there some kind of rule about writing in library books?

366
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:33,994
如果你不说的话 我也不会说出去的
I won't tell, if you don't.

367
00:20:35,385 --> 00:20:37,898
谢谢 那么 这是关于什么的?
Thank you. So, what's it about?

368
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:40,319
我不想剧透 你还是自己看吧
I don't want to spoil it for you, so you'll just have to read it yourself.

369
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,886
好吧
Deal.

370
00:20:44,873 --> 00:20:47,968
谢谢 英格丽德 谢谢你的帮助
Thank you, Ingrid, for all of your help.

371
00:20:47,969 --> 00:20:50,744
没你的帮忙这需要很久的
This would be taking so much longer without you.

372
00:20:50,762 --> 00:20:53,357
即使对极速读者来说也是吗?  
Even for Super Speed Reader Guy?  

373
00:20:53,358 --> 00:20:54,915
是的 对他也是一样
Yes, even for him.

374
00:20:55,765 --> 00:20:57,135
那么 你有我的书了 
So, you have my book. 

375
00:20:57,136 --> 00:20:58,917
我什么时候能看看你的论文?
When do I get to read your dissertation?

376
00:20:58,918 --> 00:21:03,468
不 不可能 我... 我写不完了
Oh, no. That is not happening. I... I never even finished it.

377
00:21:03,469 --> 00:21:04,761
为什么?
Why not?

378
00:21:05,199 --> 00:21:10,126
我... 我觉得对魔法的学术研究太荒谬了
I... I realized that an academic study of witchcraft was kind of ridiculous.

379
00:21:10,327 --> 00:21:13,162
这么说你不相信神喽
Ah, so you don't believe in the supernatural.

380
00:21:13,651 --> 00:21:15,235
不相信
No.

381
00:21:15,269 --> 00:21:18,238
我一直是个科学怀疑论者
Mm-mm. I'm a rational skeptic, all the way.

382
00:21:18,272 --> 00:21:21,686
那样的话 等我完成了
In that case, you probably shouldn't read the book I'm working on.

383
00:21:21,687 --> 00:21:23,543
- 你也不该读我的作品 - 为什么不呢?
- If I ever finish it. - Why not?

384
00:21:23,578 --> 00:21:25,445
我喜欢读科幻小说啊
I like science fiction and fantasy.

385
00:21:25,463 --> 00:21:27,870
- 这不是幻想 - 真的吗?
- It's not fantasy. - Really?

386
00:21:27,871 --> 00:21:29,839
这是关于女巫的 而且...
It is about witches, but...

387
00:21:30,084 --> 00:21:32,502
我相信女巫是存在的
I believe witches are real.

388
00:21:50,688 --> 00:21:52,522
有意思
Funny.

389
00:21:53,858 --> 00:21:56,046
你在哪 温迪?
Where are you, Wendy?

390
00:21:56,047 --> 00:21:58,653
你不能去那个入口
You are not going into that portal.

391
00:22:35,375 --> 00:22:37,242
不!
No!

392
00:22:40,084 --> 00:22:42,956
怎么 你打算杀了我吗? 这是你的计划吗?
So, what, are you gonna kill me? Is that the plan?

393
00:22:42,991 --> 00:22:45,959
有必要的话我会的... 除非你先杀了我
If I have to... Unless you kill me first.

394
00:22:45,994 --> 00:22:47,661
你忘了 我是永生的
You forget, I'm immortal.

395
00:22:47,695 --> 00:22:50,130
我现在知道怎么杀你了
But now I know what'll kill you.

396
00:22:50,164 --> 00:22:52,857
这个东西给了我很多好主意
This is giving me all kinds of good ideas.

397
00:22:52,858 --> 00:22:54,692
那个东西在影响你
That thing's infecting you.

398
00:22:54,702 --> 00:22:56,641
你不能相信它告诉你的
You can't believe what it's telling you.

399
00:22:56,715 --> 00:22:58,248
不 它开阔了我的眼界
No, it's opened my eyes.

400
00:22:58,266 --> 00:23:00,584
现在我知道你是一个恶魔 乔安娜
I now see that you're the evil one, Joanna.

401
00:23:00,602 --> 00:23:02,753
难怪你丈夫离你而去
No wonder your husband left you.

402
00:23:02,771 --> 00:23:06,390
唯一一个你真心爱过的男人
The only man that you ever really truly loved.

403
00:23:06,424 --> 00:23:08,609
你一样毁了他!
And you destroyed him as well!

404
00:23:08,643 --> 00:23:10,527
别把他扯进来 温迪
Leave him out of this, Wendy.

405
00:23:10,562 --> 00:23:14,031
姑娘们也不知道那些 对吧?
The girls don't know about that one, either, do they?

406
00:23:14,065 --> 00:23:16,695
你怎么和她们说她们的父亲的?
What have you told them about their father?

407
00:23:16,696 --> 00:23:18,866
她们有权利知道她们的父亲还活着 
Don't they have a right to know that he's alive 

408
00:23:18,867 --> 00:23:19,951
并且近在眼前吧?
and so close by?

409
00:23:19,988 --> 00:23:21,872
他很久之前就离开了
He left a long time ago.

410
00:23:22,410 --> 00:23:25,376
他知道我们在哪 他选择了离开
He knows where we are. He chooses to stay away.

411
00:23:25,410 --> 00:23:27,127
我好奇他为什么选择离开
I wonder why he chooses to stay away.

412
00:23:27,162 --> 00:23:29,246
是因为他无法忍受你了吗?
Is it because he can't stand the sight of you?

413
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,582
如果是的话 我可以理解
Because that one, I can understand.

414
00:23:31,616 --> 00:23:36,053
还是他无法原谅你抛下了弗雷德里克
Or is it that he can't forgive you for leaving Frederick behind.

415
00:23:36,087 --> 00:23:39,089
还是因为他无法忍受...
Or is it losing the girls...

416
00:23:39,123 --> 00:23:43,060
不断地不断地失去女儿们
Over and over and over again,

417
00:23:43,094 --> 00:23:46,291
而且因为你的错误她们才被诅咒的?
because it's your fault that they're cursed?

418
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,484
够了!
Stop!

419
00:23:52,576 --> 00:23:54,444
我知道这听起来...
I understand how it sounds...

420
00:23:54,478 --> 00:23:55,530
我过去也是个无神论者... 
I used to be a skeptic, too... 

421
00:23:55,531 --> 00:23:56,357
但是我看到了证据...
but I've seen evidence...

422
00:23:56,358 --> 00:23:58,040
我见过令人信服的证据...  
I've seen convincing evidence...  

423
00:23:58,041 --> 00:23:58,826
证据可能是假的
Evidence can be faked.

424
00:23:58,827 --> 00:24:00,949
真的有巫师的 英格丽德 
There are real witches, Ingrid, 

425
00:24:00,950 --> 00:24:03,249
活在我们中间 很好的隐藏着
living among us, hiding right in plain sight.

426
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:06,654
我相信他们很久以前从另一个世界来到这里
I believe they came here a very long time ago from a different world.

427
00:24:06,688 --> 00:24:09,723
- 仙宫 - 仙宫? 那是神话里的
- Asgard. - Asgard? This place is a myth.

428
00:24:09,741 --> 00:24:10,887
我认为它是真的 
I think it's real, 

429
00:24:10,888 --> 00:24:12,893
而且我认为它是和这个镇连着的
and I think it's actually connected to this very town.

430
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:15,029
所以你觉得有另一个世界
So you believe there's this other world

431
00:24:15,063 --> 00:24:17,832
那里会魔法的人能够来到这里
of magical people who can find their way here.

432
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:21,180
你用这种语气说出来 的确听起来很疯狂
Well, when you say it in that tone of voice, of course it sounds crazy.

433
00:24:21,181 --> 00:24:24,394
对不起 我只是 只是一时很难相信
I'm sorry, it's just, it's hard to wrap your head around it.

434
00:24:24,395 --> 00:24:26,413
听着 我没有说这个地方一定存在
Look, I'm not saying it's definitely real.

435
00:24:26,414 --> 00:24:27,831
我只是...
I just...

436
00:24:27,832 --> 00:24:29,800
希望它存在
Hope it is.

437
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:32,412
我父亲整个成年时代都在找这个地方
My father spent his entire adult life looking for it.

438
00:24:32,413 --> 00:24:36,193
- 他也是作家吗? - 不 是个考古学家
- Was he a writer, too? - No. An archaeologist.

439
00:24:36,435 --> 00:24:38,579
他... 专心于证实
He was... obsessed with proving 

440
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:41,439
这个神奇的地方的真实存在
that this mythical world was a real place.

441
00:24:41,473 --> 00:24:43,924
当然 人们都认为他疯了
Of course, people thought he was insane.

442
00:24:43,942 --> 00:24:47,778
而最后果真那样了... 他确实疯了
And eventually it came true... He did lose his mind.

443
00:24:48,328 --> 00:24:49,973
很抱歉
I'm so sorry.

444
00:24:49,974 --> 00:24:52,725
没事 没关系 几年前他去世了
No. It's okay. He died a couple years ago,

445
00:24:52,726 --> 00:24:56,237
但是在他去世之前 他给我看了他的成果
but before he went, he shared his work with me,

446
00:24:56,238 --> 00:25:01,150
恐怖的是 那些都讲得通
and... the scary thing is, it all makes sense.

447
00:25:02,410 --> 00:25:05,112
我必须证明我的父亲没有疯
I have to prove my father wasn't crazy.

448
00:25:05,130 --> 00:25:06,797
我一直研究他的成果
I've been going through his work,

449
00:25:06,832 --> 00:25:08,905
把所有的东西汇总 联系起来
putting together the pieces, connecting the dots,

450
00:25:08,906 --> 00:25:11,674
而后我发现了去仙宫的门
and what I think I've discovered the door to Asgard

451
00:25:11,675 --> 00:25:14,421
就在这里 就在东区
is here, in East End.

